transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for all that. Brooklyn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm calling about a disputed charge. I've been charged for Score Blue and I didn't order it.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry. You said you did what, sir?

Speaker 2: I've been charged.

Speaker 1: For okay, more Score Blue order and you did not order it?

Speaker 2: Okay, well, let's see what's going on. One moment.

Speaker 1: What's your first and last name? Is it Peter Jacob Jacobi, J-A-C-O-B-I?

Speaker 2: Okay, sorry, excuse me.

Speaker 1: All right, sir, so I got you pulled up here.

Speaker 2: They said—

Speaker 1: You said you didn't order this?

Speaker 2: So I ordered one time, one time.

Speaker 1: And now you're being charged for a—

Speaker 2: Subsequent shipment. No, I understand, sir. I can see you didn't set it up to order as needed.

Speaker 1: Did you? Is that what you want to do? To order as needed going forward? You don't have to receive—

Speaker 2: I mean, that's what I did initially, right?

Speaker 1: So somebody's sending you stuff you're not ordering?

Speaker 2: No, sir, because if you would have set it up to order as needed—

Speaker 1: I mean, it's fine. We give you that option, but it would never have come out this way if it was—

Speaker 2: How it came out this way. I was very consciously ordering it one time only.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I mean, then that's fine. I mean, because we give you the opportunity to do that.

Speaker 2: You just have to put as needed so we know, so you can choose again when you want your orders.

Speaker 1: But that's not done. That's the only way it goes out this way.

Speaker 2: But so basically what we said, what we'll do is we'll keep the prescription open—

Speaker 1: For the next five months here. You're going to have to call us for your next order. We are not going to send anything.

Speaker 2: What are we going to do about the charge I just got?

Speaker 1: The order that was delivered to you, yes, which you didn't order.

Speaker 2: Why did you charge me $63.75?

Speaker 1: $63.95.

Speaker 2: $63.75?

Speaker 1: $63.95.

Speaker 2: That wasn't from us then because we have here it is $63.95.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: But I didn't order it.

Speaker 1: I'd like to read—

Speaker 2: Yeah, I mean, that was a refill that went out there, sir. I do understand that you didn't order it.

Speaker 1: You can send it back if you'd like.

Speaker 2: And we can help you out with that refund.

Speaker 1: But that's totally up to you, like I said.

Speaker 2: We're going to pause everything now, and you're going to have to call for your next one in the next five months.

Speaker 1: So I don't know if you want to keep that. I'm not going to get any more for the next five months here or until you call.

Speaker 2: If I send it back, who do I send it back to? The address that it came from?

Speaker 1: Which is shipping manager. So are you never going to order as needed? I'm confused.

Speaker 2: I—

Speaker 1: You just received an order—

Speaker 2: For more Score Blue, but I did not intend to order, correct?

Speaker 1: And if all right, so since we're being clear, since we're having an understanding—

Speaker 2: When you first purchased this, we gave you the opportunity to choose. You could pick the day, every 10th—

Speaker 1: I wanted it to come out every 10th, every two months, every 15th, every four months. You can choose.

Speaker 2: Or you can put I want to order as needed.

Speaker 1: All right, so we can do that. That's what I did first order.

Speaker 2: No, no, just—I just want to make sure we're clear.

Speaker 1: We give you those options when you ordered this the first time, right? You did not choose either one.

Speaker 2: Right, and I know this because of how you received your orders, and you're saying you didn't order them. That's the proof, so—

Speaker 1: We did give you the opportunity to order as needed, sir. I understand. I don't know why it wasn't done. I get it.

Speaker 2: I don't know why it wasn't done. That's not the point. The point is we can change it for you—

Speaker 1: Now, and we can help you out.

Speaker 2: Yeah, we're not trying to scam you or anything like that, sir.

Speaker 1: We just want to be clear. You want to be clear, and let's be clear about this.

Speaker 2: I do not want any more sent to me, okay?

Speaker 1: Wonderful, okay. I'm just glad that you understand what's going on now, sir. We can do that for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, all right, so I'm stuck with that order now, so I'm stuck with a $62 charge.

Speaker 1: I was very clear in what I told you to do with that charge previous to what I said, sir.

Speaker 2: Do you not remember what I told you? Yeah, I think I could send it back to you, okay?

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: That's what we'll do.
